The paper deals with natural language processing techniques to extract structured information from biomedical manuscripts. Specifically, it focuses on extracting author contributions from scientific publications. This falls under the domain of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also uses statistical analysis and machine learning techniques, which are common in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and deep learning (cs.DL). Finally, the paper deals with biomedical data, which could also fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
